Action: Ensure that CSS :before and :after pseudo-elements are not employed for inserting non-decorative content.
 How to fix:
1. Use informative content directly in html (OR)
2. If it is a informative image use alt text in the content itself like  content: url(./img/star.png) / "New!";
3. If it is decorative image use empty alt like content: "\02795" / "";
